column106: description:"FACT-Kidney Symptom Index-Disease Related Symptoms (FKSI-DRS) subscale of the FKSI to measure advanced kidney cancer disease related symptoms. Includes 9 items: lack of energy
column114: and hematuria. Each question was answered on a five-point Likert-type scale ranging from 0 (not at all) to 4 (very much). Score = the sum score of the item scores in the subscale; total range: 0 to 36. A score greater than 0 indicates the difference favored sunitinib."

column117: description:"FACT-Kidney Symptom Index (FKSI) subscale designed to be a stand-alone instrument to measure symptoms and quality of life in patients with advanced kidney cancer. Contains 15 questions; some questions overlap with the FACT-G questions. Each question was answered on a five-point Likert-type scale ranging from 0 to 4 (0=not at all
column121: 4=very much). Total FKSI score = sum score of the 15 item scores; total range: 0 - 60; 0 (most severe symptoms and concerns) to 60 (no symptoms or concerns)."
column122: timeFrame:"Day 1 & 28 of each cycle: duration of treatment phase"}
column124: description:"Functional Assessment of Cancer Therapy-General (FACT-G): core questionnaire of the Functional Assessment of Chronic Illness Therapy (FACIT) measurement system that has been validated in a variety of cancer populations. 27 questions grouped into 4 domains that measure a patient's physical
column127: and emotional well-being. Five-point Likert-type scale ranging from 0 to 4 (0=not at all
column131: 4=very much). Score = sum score of item scores in the subscale; total range: 0 to 108 with higher score indicating better quality of life."
column132: timeFrame:"Day 1 & 28 of each cycle: duration of treatment phase"}

column162: description:"EQ-5D Health State Index: a brief
column163: self-administered generic health status instrument. Respondents were asked to describe their current health state on each of 5 dimensions (mobility
column167: and anxiety or depression) on a three-level scale (1=no problem
column169: and 3=extreme problem). A maximum score of 1 can be derived from these 5 dimensions by score conversion; range: -0.39 (worst health state)to 1.00 (best health state). This descriptive system classifies respondents into one of 243 possible distinct health states (EQ-5D descriptive system)."

column172: description:"EQ-VAS: overall self-rating rating of the patient's current health state using a 20 cm Visual Analog Scale (EQ-VAS)
column173: also called the health state thermometer) is a metric measurement (in 2 mm interval) from the visual analog scale which ranges between 0 (worse imaginable health state) and 100 (best imaginable health state)."

Soluble protein values: Baseline concentration (pM) and ratio to Baseline at each timepoint; ratio = plasma concentration of soluble protein (picograms per milliliter \\[pg/ml\\]) at timepoint / concentration of soluble protein (pg/ml) at baseline. column188: description:"Incremental cost effectiveness ratio (ICER) of sunitinib compared to IFN-a as first-line treatment for MRCC
column189: defined as the ratio of the incremental cost of treatment over the incremental effectiveness; effectiveness measured as quality adjusted life year (QALY) gain. This objective was not addressed in the clinical study report
column190: but an interim analysis of cost-effectiveness was presented separately. These results were not available for inclusion at the time of this posting."
column193: description:"Subject observed Ctrough (trough drug) concentrations of SU011248 per cycle and study day determined by plasma trough samples collected from a subset of patients. eligibilityModule:{"eligibilityCriteria":"Inclusion Criteria:

* Histologically confirmed renal cell carcinoma of clear cell histology with metastases
* Evidence of measurable disease by radiographic technique
* Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group \[ECOG\] performance status of 0 or 1

Exclusion Criteria:

* Prior systemic (including adjuvant or neoadjuvant) therapy of any kind for RCC
* History of or known brain metastases
* Serious acute or chronic illness or recent history of significant cardiac abnormality"

column2687: description:"FACT-Kidney Symptom Index (FKSI) subscale designed to be a stand-alone instrument to measure symptoms and quality of life in patients with advanced kidney cancer. Contains 15 questions; some questions overlap with the FACT-G questions. Each question was answered on a five-point Likert-type scale ranging from 0 to 4 (0=not at all
column2691: 4=very much). Total FKSI score = sum score of the 15 item scores; total range: 0 - 60; 0 (most severe symptoms and concerns) to 60 (no symptoms or concerns)."
column2692: populationDescription:"ITT; N=number of subjects with evaluable data; n=number of subjects with evaluable data at observation."
column2697: timeFrame:"Day 1 & 28 of each cycle: duration of treatment phase"

column8817: title:"EuroQoL Five Dimension (EQ-5D) Health State Index"
column8818: description:"EQ-5D Health State Index: a brief
column8819: self-administered generic health status instrument. Respondents were asked to describe their current health state on each of 5 dimensions (mobility
column8823: and anxiety or depression) on a three-level scale (1=no problem
column8825: and 3=extreme problem). A maximum score of 1 can be derived from these 5 dimensions by score conversion; range: -0.39 (worst health state)to 1.00 (best health state). This descriptive system classifies respondents into one of 243 possible distinct health states (EQ-5D descriptive system)."
